/* Handling links in citations */ How come we don't have a shortcut to this? This must be illegal.
/* How to create the list of citations */ +{{Shortcut|WP:REFLIST}} per [[Wikipedia:Redirects for discussion/Log/2019 November 27#Wikipedia:REFLIST]]
/* General references */ A reference is still a reference if it isn't reliable.

/* Citing multiple pages of the same source */ CE to also list the most commonly used method of citing multiple pages of the same source: just combine the page numbers of the invocations of a citation into a single list (works well for as long as the number of individual pages does not become too large). I wonder how this common pragmatic method could not be mentioned here - it is even referred to as being described here in the following section on duplicate citations...
